THE Rutanang Primary School in the North West will be closed until Monday, 6 June. The provincial education department has temporarily closed the school following the shooting of grade R teacher Penelope Nxumalo. She was killed at the school gate as she arrived on Tuesday, 31 May at about 7am. Nxumalo was in her Toyota Fortuner when two men approached and shot her at close range. Nothing was taken from the car. The paramedics declared her dead at the scene. North West education MEC Mmaphefo Matsemela said she was disappointed that the social ills from the community were finding expression at schools. “Our schools are a reflection of what is happening in our communities. It’s time that we reflect on the challenges facing our schools,” she said. “I believe the police will find those behind the horrible incident.” ALSO READ | Senior journalist turned Shakes Mashaba’s taxi
driver Matsemela conveyed her condolences to the family and the entire school community. North West police spokesman Brigadier Sabata Mokgwabone said the motive behind the incident was yet to be determined. “Investigation into the matter continues and no arrest has been made,” said Mokgwabone. The police request that anyone who may have information that can help the police to contact Lieutenant-Colonel Partson Chomela on 082 772 8124. Provincial police commissioner Lieutenant-General Sello Kwena expressed shock over the callous act. He urged members of the community to work with the police to ensure that the suspects were brought to book.